25|$|Whenever {{a hazard}} is played, any player holding the {{corresponding}} safety may immediately play it and declare a coup-fourré. This may be done {{whether or not}} the player holding the safety was the one attacked by the hazard. The safety is laid down horizontally in the <b>safety</b> <b>area,</b> and the player draws a new card and takes his/her normal turn, skipping all players between the attacker and him/herself. In addition, if he/she was attacked with the hazard, it is moved to the discard pile.|$|E
