40|$|A {{summary of}} the {{technical}} results and conclusions is presented of the hazards analyses of earth orbital operations {{in conjunction with the}} space shuttle program. The space shuttle orbiter and a variety of manned and unmanned payloads delivered to orbit by the shuttle are considered. The specific <b>safety</b> <b>areas</b> examined are hazardous payloads, docking, on-orbit survivability, tumbling spacecraft, and escape and rescue...|$|R
